      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i just got this NDA from a potential partner and i dont really want to pay a lawyer just to read it yet. can u just give me a quick summary of the main parts? like what counts as confidential, how long does this last for, and what happens if someone breaks the rules? thanks.\n\n[DOCUMENT START]\nNON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement (the \"Agreement\") is entered into as of October 14, 2023, by and between Zenith Solutions LLC (\"Disclosing Party\") and BrightPath Ventures Inc. (\"Receiving Party\").\n\n1. Definition of Confidential Information. \"Confidential Information\" shall include all non-public, proprietary, or sensitive information, whether oral, written, or electronic, disclosed by the Disclosing Party, including but not limited to business plans, customer lists, software code, and financial projections.\n\n2. Obligations of Receiving Party. The Receiving Party agrees to hold the Confidential Information in strict confidence and to use such information solely for the purpose of evaluating a potential business relationship. The Receiving Party shall implement reasonable security measures to prevent unauthorized disclosure.\n\n3. Term and Termination. This Agreement shall remain in effect for a period of three (3) years from the date of disclosure of the relevant Confidential Information. The obligations of confidentiality with respect to trade secrets shall survive indefinitely.\n\n4. Remedies for Breach. The Receiving Party acknowledges that unauthorized disclosure could cause irreparable harm for which monetary damages may be inadequate. Therefore, the Disclosing Party shall be entitled to seek injunctive relief in addition to any other legal remedies available.\n\n[DOCUMENT END]",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
